02:23.300 --> 02:27.180
So you're worried about this 
Nagi-san lady who has a bun in the oven,

02:27.180 --> 02:28.760
and you want to go check on her?

02:29.010 --> 02:32.950
Well, purely in terms of how I feel, 
that's what it boils down to, yeah.

02:33.260 --> 02:34.220
Okay!

02:34.220 --> 02:36.770
Forget the nitty-gritty. Let's go, Nio-kun!

02:36.770 --> 02:38.660
Th-Thank you.

02:38.840 --> 02:41.600
Talk about simple. Is that lady okay?

02:42.360 --> 02:43.880
Heisuke! Soji!

02:44.200 --> 02:45.950
We ain't got swords.

02:45.950 --> 02:48.140
Lend us something! We'll settle for daggers!

02:48.320 --> 02:49.280
Please!

02:49.280 --> 02:50.690
Wh-Why?

02:51.010 --> 02:56.050
Oh, right. You pawned your swords 
and lost the money gambling.

02:56.570 --> 02:57.790
Guess we have no choice.

02:58.830 --> 03:00.120
I owe you one.

03:00.300 --> 03:01.400
You'd better return it!

03:01.400 --> 03:02.810
All right, all right.

03:03.240 --> 03:07.370
They wanna set Kyoto on fire?
What a bunch of showoffs.

03:07.370 --> 03:09.870
We'll show 'em what the Miburo are made of.

03:10.030 --> 03:12.040
Stay on your toes, Yamanami.

03:12.400 --> 03:13.880
I don't need you to tell me that.

03:15.240 --> 03:18.430
I don't wanna die! I don't wanna die!

03:18.430 --> 03:19.720
Shut up.

03:20.120 --> 03:21.800
It's the second bridge after the corner.

03:21.800 --> 03:22.960
I know.

03:23.180 --> 03:25.230
Noguchi, you're with me.

03:25.230 --> 03:26.440
Don't fall behind.

03:26.440 --> 03:28.400
Y-Yes, sir! Sorry!

03:40.310 --> 03:42.120
This wind is a problem.

03:42.750 --> 03:46.500
If they start a fire on this side of 
the bridges, it'll spread in a flash.

03:48.720 --> 03:49.460
Look.

03:49.750 --> 03:51.680
The Sanjo Bridge!

03:52.100 --> 03:53.120
Smoke signals!

03:53.120 --> 03:54.760
They're going up all over the place!

03:55.240 --> 03:56.640
Here they come!

03:56.640 --> 03:57.590
Spread out!

03:57.880 --> 03:58.880
Yeah!

